==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infusibility
<hw>In*fu`si*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Infuse</er>.]</ety> <def>Capability of being infused, poured in, or
instilled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infusibility</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Infusibility
<hw>In*fu`si*bil"i*ty</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>in-</ets> not
+ <ets>fusibility</ets>: cf. F. <ets>infusibilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Incapability or difficulty of being fused, melted, or dissolved;
<as>as, the <ex>infusibility</ex> of carbon</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infusible</ent>⟦br⟧
